OL,3,CCumbrian MP welcomes new road safety
OL,4,Cmeasures
OL,6,FCouncillor Peter Thornton, Westmorland
OL,7,Fand Furness Council Cabinet Member for
OL,8,FHighways and ICT, says it is "a
OL,9,Fcrucial first step" in committing to
OL,10,Froad safety in the area.
OL,12,FHe said: "Unfortunately there have
OL,13,Fbeen a number of serious collisions at
OL,14,FJunction 37 of the M6. As a part of
OL,15,FCumbria's Road Safety Partnership, the
OL,16,FCouncil have been working together
OL,17,Fwith National Highways to urgently
OL,18,Faddress the concerns of our residents
OL,19,Fand consider traffic management
OL,20,Fmeasures on their slip road.
